You are analyzing code for **Mass Assignment** vulnerabilities.

## What Is Mass Assignment?

Mass assignment occurs when an application takes user-supplied input (request body, query params, form data) and passes it directly into an ORM create or update call without filtering which fields the user is allowed to set. An attacker can inject extra fields (e.g., `role: "admin"`, `isVerified: true`) to escalate privileges or corrupt data.

